rom\": 750, \"to\": 763}, {\"ngram\": \"events\", \"from\": 767, \"to\": 773}, {\"ngram\": \"the programme\", \"from\": 804, \"to\": 817}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Golds forTom Pidcockon the mountain and the women's track sprint team of Katy Marchant, Sophie Capewell and Emma Finucane were backed up by five silver and four bronze medals - including two of the latter for Finucane, one of the star performers of these Games.\", \"from\": 820, \"to\": 1081, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 893, \"end\": 906, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Katy_Marchant\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Katy Marchant\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Katy_Marchant\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Katy_Marchant\"}, {\"begin\": 908, \"end\": 923, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Sophie_Capewell\", \"score\": 0.999997246383526, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Sophie Capewell\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Sophie_Capewell\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Sophie_Capewell\"}, {\"begin\": 928, \"end\": 932, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Emma_Swan\", \"score\": 0.6552213570196522, \"rank\": 0.4980476849881452, \"text\": \"Emma\", \"types\": [\"Q95074\", \"Q24229398\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Emma_Swan\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Emma_Swan\"}], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"Golds forTom\", \"from\": 820, \"to\": 832}, {\"ngram\": \"Pidcockon\", \"from\": 833, \"to\": 842}, {\"ngram\": \"the mountain\", \"from\": 843, \"to\": 855}, {\"ngram\": \"the women's track sprint team\", \"from\": 860, \"to\": 889}, {\"ngram\": \"five silver\", \"from\": 960, \"to\": 971}, {\"ngram\": \"four bronze medals\", \"from\": 976, \"to\": 994}, {\"ngram\": \"Finucane\", \"from\": 1029, \"to\": 1037}, {\"ngram\": \"the star performers\", \"from\": 1046, \"to\": 1065}, {\"ngram\": \"these Games\", \"from\": 1069, \"to\": 1080}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Athletics also saw a double-figure haul, the highlight being Keely Hodgkinson's 800 metres gold.\", \"from\": 1083, \"to\": 1179, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 1144, \"end\": 1160, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Keely_Hodgkinson\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Keely Hodgkinson\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Keely_Hodgkinson\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Keely_Hodgkinson\"}], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"Athletics\", \"from\": 1083, \"to\": 1092}, {\"ngram\": \"a double-figure haul\", \"from\": 1102, \"to\": 1122}, {\"ngram\": \"the highlight\", \"from\": 1124, \"to\": 1137}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Britain won medals in all five relays - four bronzes, and silver in the women's 4x100m.\", \"from\": 1180, \"to\": 1267, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 1180, \"end\": 1187, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Great_Britain\", \"score\": 0.9999991990715468, \"rank\": 8.00928996293264e-07, \"text\": \"Britain\", \"types\": [\"Q23442\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Great_Britain\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Great_Britain\"}], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"medals\", \"from\": 1192, \"to\": 1198}, {\"ngram\": \"all five relays - four bronzes\", \"from\": 1202, \"to\": 1232}, {\"ngram\": \"silver\", \"from\": 1238, \"to\": 1244}, {\"ngram\": \"the women's 4x100m.\", \"from\": 1248, \"to\": 1267}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Team GB's rowers made a major return to form with three gold, two silver and three bronze medals.\", \"from\": 1269, \"to\": 1366, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 1269, \"end\": 1276, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Team_GB\", \"score\": 0.9999999999970441, \"rank\": 2.8905476933139806e-12, \"text\": \"Team GB\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Team_GB\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Team_GB\"}], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"a major return\", \"from\": 1291, \"to\": 1305}, {\"ngram\": \"three gold\", \"from\": 1319, \"to\": 1329}, {\"ngram\": \"two silver\", \"from\": 1331, \"to\": 1341}, {\"ngram\": \"three bronze medals\", \"from\": 1346, \"to\": 1365}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Gold came from the men's eight and the women's quadruple sculls and lightweight double sculls.\", \"from\": 1368, \"to\": 1462, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"Gold\", \"from\": 1368, \"to\": 1372}, {\"ngram\": \"the women's quadruple sculls\", \"from\": 1403, \"to\": 1431}, {\"ngram\": \"lightweight double sculls\", \"from\": 1436, \"to\": 1461}]}, {\"sentence\": \"The women's pair and the men's quadruple sculls were the only British boats not to win medals, with the latter finishing fourth.\", \"from\": 1463, \"to\": 1591, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 1525, \"end\": 1532, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Great_Britain\", \"score\": 0.9999968636915652, \"rank\": 3.079212959413754e-06, \"text\": \"British\", \"types\": [\"Q23442\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Great_Britain\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Great_Britain\"}], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"The women's pair\", \"from\": 1463, \"to\": 1479}, {\"ngram\": \"the men's quadruple sculls\", \"from\": 1484, \"to\": 1510}, {\"ngram\": \"medals\", \"from\": 1550, \"to\": 1556}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Equestrian was another typical success story, despite the pre-Games controversy around Charlotte Dujardin, with team golds in eventing and jumping and bronze for Laura Collett in jumping and for the team and Charlotte Fry individually in dressage.\", \"from\": 1593, \"to\": 1840, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 1680, \"end\": 1698, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Charlotte_Dujardin\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Charlotte Dujardin\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Charlotte_Dujardin\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Charlotte_Dujard